cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on wireless sensor networks and their communication protocols. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper discusses cooperative processing between sensors. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with synchronization of clocks in a network. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper evaluates different synchronization algorithms. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses energy-efficient information processing and routing in WSNs.
